The '''Indrexu Confederation''' was one of the feuding states that rose in the [[Tion Cluster/Legends|Tion Cluster]] from the ashes of [[Xim/Legends|Xim the Despot's]] [[Xim's empire|empire]], a century after his [[Death/Legends|death]]. The region, originally called [[Far Indrexu]], was discovered during the expansion of Xim's empire circa [[25,100 BBY]].<ref name="Xim Week">{{SW|url=news/essential-atlas-extra-the-history-of-xim-and-the-tion-cluster|text=Essential Atlas Extra: The History of Xim and the Tion Cluster|int=Xim Week: The History of Xim and the Tion Cluster}}</ref>

It disappeared when the cluster joined the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Republic]]. Millennia after, it was recreated on the same area as the [[Indrexu sector/Legends|Indrexu sector]], when the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]] split the [[Tion Hegemony/Legends|Tion Hegemony]] in multiple sectors.<ref name="Xim Week" />

Notable worlds included [[Ank Ki'Shor]], [[Janodral Mizar]], [[Estaria/Legends|Estaria]] and [[Endregaad]].<ref name="Xim Week" />

